stun/tools (stund, stunbdc) is the only unconditional subdir — the
examples/tests options gate everything else. As a subproject only
libnice/libstun are consumed, so the standalone STUN daemon and client
are dead weight in the parent build.

---
 stun/meson.build | 5 ++++-
 1 file changed, 4 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/stun/meson.build b/stun/meson.build
--- a/stun/meson.build
+++ b/stun/meson.build
@@ -34,7 +34,10 @@
   dependencies: nice_deps,
   install: false)

-subdir('tools')
+# As a subproject, skip the stund/stunbdc command-line tools.
+if not meson.is_subproject()
+  subdir('tools')
+endif

 if not get_option('tests').disabled()
   subdir('tests')
